initial statement:
 1061
Your Honor, 

I stand before you today, pleading guilty to the charge of careless driving. I accept full responsibility for my actions and deeply regret the consequences that followed. 

On the day in question, I was on my way to the airport to pick up my family members. In my haste, I drove aggressively and exceeded the speed limit. Regrettably, I also made the poor decision to answer a text message while behind the wheel. As a result, I lost control of my vehicle and collided with a guardrail. Fortunately, no one else was harmed in the incident. 

Reflecting on this incident, I now realize the immense danger I put myself and others in by my reckless driving behavior. I acknowledge the gravity of my actions and the potential harm that could have resulted. 

I am aware that I already have 3 penalty points on my driving license for a previous speeding offense. This serves as a stark reminder of the importance of adhering to traffic laws and driving responsibly. 

However, I would like to bring to your attention that, outside of this incident, I have maintained a clean record. Additionally, I have been an active supporter of the British Heart Foundation, regularly making donations to their cause. I believe this exemplifies my commitment to being a responsible and contributing member of society. 

I understand that my plea of guilty will serve as a mitigating factor in this case. It demonstrates my willingness to accept the consequences of my actions and take responsibility for the harm caused. 

While I acknowledge the seriousness of my offense, I would like to assure the court that I have learned from this experience. I am genuinely remorseful for my actions and I am committed to making changes in my behavior to prevent a similar incident from happening again. 

In conclusion, I stand before the court today, pleading guilty to careless driving. I accept the consequences of my actions and hope that the court will consider my genuine remorse and commitment to personal growth in determining an appropriate sentence. Thank you for your attention.
