NEW STATEMENT:

1168
Your Honor,

I appear before the court today to enter a plea of guilty for the charge of careless driving. I take full responsibility for my actions and deeply regret the consequences that followed. By pleading guilty, I hope to demonstrate my acceptance of accountability.

On the day in question, I was rushing to the airport to pick up my family members. In my haste, I admit that I drove aggressively, exceeding the prescribed speed limit. To compound this dangerous behavior, I made the misguided decision to read and respond to a text message while operating the vehicle. Tragically, this led to an accident where I collided with a guardrail. Thankfully, no one else suffered any injuries.

Reflecting upon this incident, I now recognize the immense peril I exposed both myself and others to through my reckless driving. I acknowledge the severity of my actions and the potential harm they could have caused.

I am aware that I bear three penalty points on my driving license due to a prior speeding offense. This serves as a stark reminder of the need to adhere strictly to traffic regulations and to prioritize responsible driving.

However, I would like to bring to the court's attention that, aside from this unfortunate incident, I maintain an otherwise clean record. Moreover, I am an active supporter of the British Heart Foundation, consistently making donations to aid their cause. I believe this underscores my commitment to being an upstanding member of society and reinforces my genuine remorse for my actions.

Recognizing the significance of my plea, I assure the court of my willingness to face the consequences of my actions and take full responsibility for the harm caused. I am acutely aware of the gravity of my offense, and I pledge to learn from this experience. I truly regret my actions and remain committed to making the necessary changes in behavior to prevent a recurrence of such an incident.

In conclusion, I come before the court today, pleading guilty to the charge of careless driving. I acknowledge the ramifications of my actions and implore the court to consider my sincere remorse, my dedication to personal growth, and the fact that my plea of guilt is a mitigating factor that benefits the court. I am appreciative of your attention and thank you for considering these mitigating circumstances.
