On the day in question, I was on my way to the airport to pick up my family members. Due to being pressed for time, I drove aggressively and exceeded the speed limit. Additionally, I made the ill-advised decision to answer a text message while I was behind the wheel. As a result, I collided with a guardrail, fortunately without causing harm to anyone else involved.

Upon reflecting on this incident, I now recognize the immense danger I exposed not only myself but also others to through my careless actions. I fully acknowledge the severity of my actions and the potential harm they could have caused to both myself and others.

I am aware that I already have three penalty points on my driving license for a previous speeding offense. This serves as a stark reminder to me of the importance of adhering to traffic regulations, and I deeply regret failing to do so on this occasion.

In conclusion, I sincerely accept my guilt in the charge of careless driving. I understand the consequences that come with my actions, and I extend my heartfelt apologies for any harm caused. I kindly request the court's leniency and assure you that I have learned a valuable lesson from this experience. Thank you for your attention to this matter.

Sincerely,
