NEW STATEMENT:

957
Your Honor,

I am writing to express my sincere remorse and to plead guilty to the charge of careless driving. I take full responsibility for my actions and deeply regret the consequences that resulted from my careless behavior.

On the day in question, I was on my way to the airport to pick up my family members. Due to being pressed for time, I made the regrettable decision to drive aggressively and exceed the speed limit. In a moment of distraction, I also answered a text message from my cousin while behind the wheel. Unfortunately, this led to a collision with a guardrail.

Reflecting on this incident, I am filled with profound remorse and deep regret for endangering not only myself but also others on the road that day. I understand now the immense danger my reckless actions posed to everyone around me, and I sincerely apologize for my thoughtlessness.

I humbly admit that I already have three penalty points on my driving license for a previous speeding offense. This serves as a stark reminder to me of the importance of adhering to traffic regulations, and I deeply regret my failure to do so on this occasion.

Allow me to take a moment to discuss my character and personal circumstances. I am 37 years old, with an otherwise clean record. As evidence of my commitment to others' well-being, I make regular donations to the British Heart Foundation. I assure you that the incident in question was a grave lapse in judgment and does not reflect my true character.

In conclusion, I wholeheartedly accept my guilt in the charge of careless driving. I genuinely comprehend the consequences of my actions and extend my heartfelt apologies for any harm caused. I kindly request the court's leniency and assure you that this experience has been a pivotal lesson for me. Thank you for your consideration.

Sincerely,
Charlotte Porter
